Topic - Basic Commands

ls: list directory contents
pwd: print the name of current, working diretory
whoami: print username
hostname: print hostname
cd: change directory
mv: move file or directory/ change the name of directory or file
touch: create new basic file
rm: remove file or directory
mkdir: create new directory
rmdir: remove directory(command only axecute when directory is empty)
echo: display input text to standard output
vi/nano: standard file editor
